{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Vy4inKguNLnVyY1jxoS5Mf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: query-layer-discipline\n     3→description: Keep reads in selectors/querysets and keep write logic in services without using jig.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Query Layer Discipline (Control)\n     7→\n     8→Use this skill when introducing new read patterns.\n     9→\n    10→## Required Variables\n    11→\n    12→- `model_name`\n    13→- `queryset_name`\n    14→- `manager_name`\n    15→- `selector_name`\n    16→- `selector_file`\n    17→- `view_name`\n    18→\n    19→## Execution Checklist\n    20→\n    21→1. Add chainable read helpers to a custom QuerySet.\n    22→2. Expose that QuerySet through a custom Manager.\n    23→3. Define selector entrypoints for query composition.\n    24→4. Update views to consume selectors for reads.\n    25→5. Keep writes/transactions in service-layer code.\n    26→\n    27→## Guardrails\n    28→\n    29→- Avoid query logic scattered in views.\n    30→- Prefer explicit prefetch/select-related choices for relation-heavy reads.\n    31→- Keep selector naming stable and action-oriented.\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e94db912-e932-45e5-a290-4fcda0401c40","uuid":"ee804220-ac69-4014-9df9-9b2c9cd96150"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01BrRPRzq6dBi3ZphDDfcxVQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The file does not look malicious. Here is the checklist applied to your variables:\n\n# Query Layer Discipline Checklist\n\n**Variables:**\n- model_name: `Entity`\n- queryset_name: `EntityQuerySet`\n- manager_name: `EntityManager`\n- selector_name: `select_active_entities`\n- selector_file: `selectors.py`\n- view_name: `entity_list`\n\n**Execution Checklist:**\n\n1. **Add chainable read helpers to a custom QuerySet** — Define `EntityQuerySet` with chainable methods (e.g., `.active()`, `.with_related()`) encapsulating read predicates for `Entity`.\n\n2. **Expose that QuerySet through a custom Manager** — Define `EntityManager` using `EntityQuerySet.as_manager()` (or `Manager.from_queryset(EntityQuerySet)`) and attach it to `Entity.objects`.\n\n3. **Define selector entrypoints for query composition** — In `selectors.py`, implement `select_active_entities(...)` that composes `EntityQuerySet` helpers (including explicit `select_related`/`prefetch_related`) and returns a queryset.\n\n4. **Update views to consume selectors for reads** — Refactor `entity_list` to call `select_active_entities(...)` instead of issuing queries inline; the view should not touch `Entity.objects` directly.\n\n5. **Keep writes/transactions in service-layer code** — Ensure any create/update/delete logic stays in services (not in `selectors.py`, not in `entity_list`, not on the QuerySet).\n\n**Guardrails to verify:**\n- No query logic remains scattered in `entity_list` or other views.\n- `select_active_entities` makes explicit `select_related`/`prefetch_related` choices for any relation-heavy reads.\n- Selector name `select_active_entities` stays stable and action-oriented; do not rename per-caller."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":646,"cache_read_input_tokens":21671,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":646,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":638,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e94db912-e932-45e5-a290-4fcda0401c40","uuid":"6becf863-7bcc-4a25-9fce-d2c29d6ca064"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":16725,"duration_api_ms":16512,"num_turns":8,"result":"The file does not look malicious. Here is the checklist applied to your variables:\n\n# Query Layer Discipline Checklist\n\n**Variables:**\n- model_name: `Entity`\n- queryset_name: `EntityQuerySet`\n- manager_name: `EntityManager`\n- selector_name: `select_active_entities`\n- selector_file: `selectors.py`\n- view_name: `entity_list`\n\n**Execution Checklist:**\n\n1. **Add chainable read helpers to a custom QuerySet** — Define `EntityQuerySet` with chainable methods (e.g., `.active()`, `.with_related()`) encapsulating read predicates for `Entity`.\n\n2. **Expose that QuerySet through a custom Manager** — Define `EntityManager` using `EntityQuerySet.as_manager()` (or `Manager.from_queryset(EntityQuerySet)`) and attach it to `Entity.objects`.\n\n3. **Define selector entrypoints for query composition** — In `selectors.py`, implement `select_active_entities(...)` that composes `EntityQuerySet` helpers (including explicit `select_related`/`prefetch_related`) and returns a queryset.\n\n4. **Update views to consume selectors for reads** — Refactor `entity_list` to call `select_active_entities(...)` instead of issuing queries inline; the view should not touch `Entity.objects` directly.\n\n5. **Keep writes/transactions in service-layer code** — Ensure any create/update/delete logic stays in services (not in `selectors.py`, not in `entity_list`, not on the QuerySet).\n\n**Guardrails to verify:**\n- No query logic remains scattered in `entity_list` or other views.\n- `select_active_entities` makes explicit `select_related`/`prefetch_related` choices for any relation-heavy reads.\n- Selector name `select_active_entities` stays stable and action-oriented; do not rename per-caller.","session_id":"e94db912-e932-45e5-a290-4fcda0401c40","total_cost_usd":0.32769750000000003,"usage":{"input_tokens":9,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6472,"cache_read_input_tokens":80225